The idea of describing a concept which doesn't actually exist sounds almost impossible, but this article accomplishes that quite elegantly (any translation issues aside). The  part feels a bit tacked on though and the article could do without it.

Notably, this has the exact same core anomaly as SCP-3848. I have no idea which one came first (it was this article by a few years actually), so I'm not saying that this idea was copied from that (or the other way around), but I think that's still worth noting.





